 get ur specialization of say evocation over 50, can u still get ur other specialization skills to 50 too? or is it not even important getting it to 50 since it wont reduce any mana? Im not even sure if the specialization stuff is helping my mana, i stil cant tell the diference. and im at 24 with magi now.. could sure use on  help on this.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Daimyen<br>
24 mage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvumil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vumil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Lich</span><br>  Posts: 1102<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/15/01 9:51:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Specialization ? for first time caster player..</span><hr size=1> you can only have one specialization over 50.  It does help out alot, most people probably don't notice because its just there, but if a spell cost 200mana and you had a 1000 mana, you would know its helping out when you can cast the spell 6-7times <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uresomatic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Res O Matic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Templar of Tipsy</span><br>  Posts: 439<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/16/01 2:51:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Specialization ? for first time caster player..</span><hr size=1> Basically, get the spell group you use the most over 50, and don't worry about the other ones.  Alteration is the way to go for a cleric, evocation for a wizard, that kind of thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usubatirazorback.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Subati Razorback</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/17/01 7:41:03 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.dalbers.homestead.com/files/subpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Specialization ? for first time caster player..</span><hr size=1> I maxxed out Alteration for my mage, and Im glad I did.<br>
<br>
When you get 3 raptors all smacking you for 100 points at a whallop, gate goes off and saves your arse.<br>
<br>
Now, that my soloing days are over, I may do the quest and reset them back to 50, and go with Evok. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uriggen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Riggen</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Roving Eye of Serilis</span><br>  Posts: 474<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/17/01 3:15:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Specialization ? for first time caster player..</span><hr size=1> Specialization helps with mana cost and fizzle rates, but it doesn't have any effect on interruption. That's the role of Channeling.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utrylliumcalaquendi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tryllium Calaquendi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/20/01 12:11:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eatel.net/~usafcajun/drunks/sigpics/sigpictryllium.gif width=80 height=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Specialization ? for first time caster player..</span><hr size=1> You say you're 24 and you haven't noticed any difference?  Wait until you get into the 40's my friend, and you certainly <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> will</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> see a difference, I did!  My specialization is Alteration (cleric <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) and when it really kicks in I can buff the whole party in one shot and not be totally out of mana (15 buffs total).<br>
<br>
My husband plays a mage (lvl44) who originally specialized in Evocation since he got so few Conjuration-based damage spells... now that he's 44 however he's doing the quest and changing his spec to Conjuration since Shock of Blades (I think that's right!) is now his primary DD.<br>
<br>
I think mages are the only ones (I could be really wrong tho) who get kinda hosed about their &quot;best&quot; damage spells sometimes being Evoc and sometimes being Conjur. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rayster>Rayster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/20/01 7:31:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Specialization ? for first time caster player..</span><hr size=1> Hmm, I thought cleric buff spells like symbol, resolution and AC buff are all &quot;Abjuration&quot;.  I could be wrong.<br>
<br>
Rayster <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uariannda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ariannda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Brell's Babymage</span><br>  Posts: 1391<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/20/01 10:25:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Specialization ? for first time caster player..</span><hr size=1> most mages i know are conj since we're summoners, but personally i'm doing evocation. Talk to some higher mages in game, or make friends with them so they can answer any questions you might have with their own reference <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Really it DOES depend on the player, but mage go conj or evoc <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
